faultGuidance.AdditionalInformation: An emissions fault has occurred. This fault may set following fuel system service. Return to servicing facility for follow up action if recently serviced. Continued operation is possible if no other faults are present and engine is running as expected. No power derate. No pending power derate.
PossibleCauses: Malfunction of one or both of the common rail unit pumps
Air present in the fuel system
Malfunction of the common rail high pressure release valve
Malfunction of one or more of the fuel injectors
Faulty wiring between the engine ECU and the common rail fuel pressure sensor
faultGuidance.DTCDescription: Engine fuel rail pressure not in expected range.
